external_knowledge:
- Top 5 locations refers to the locations with the highest average pollution level index; 
- Weekend of May 26-27 refers to the data collected on 'Friday, May 26' and 'Saturday, May 27'; 
- Worst air quality refers to the highest average pollution level index.

External knowledge:
- Pollution level index is a quantifiable measure of air quality, with higher values indicating poorer air quality; 
- Cumulative pollution level index is calculated by summing up the pollution level index values ordered by the creation timestamp, providing a sense of the trend over time.

sql:
SELECT temperature_high, temperature_low
FROM air_quality_data
WHERE day = 'Friday, May 26';

SELECT AVG(pollution_level_index) AS average_pollution_index
FROM air_quality_data
WHERE location_id = (SELECT id FROM locations WHERE name = 'New York City');
